# Ignore patterns for `tauri dev`'s file watcher — REPO-ROOT scope.
#
# Why this file lives here (and not only in gui/src-tauri/):
#
# The Tauri GUI crate (`gui/src-tauri`) declares a path dependency on
# the repo-root crate (`bastion_vault = { path = "../.." }`), so Tauri
# adds the **repo root** to its watch folders and recurses the whole
# tree. Tauri roots each `.taurignore` it finds at that file's OWN
# parent directory, so `gui/src-tauri/.taurignore` only governs files
# under `gui/src-tauri/` — its `plugins-ext/` / `IronRDP/` lines never
# matched the repo-root dirs of the same name. (repo-root `target/` is
# silenced by Tauri's built-in ignore list, which is why it looked like
# the gui file was working.)
#
# This root-level file is the one that actually stops writes under
# `plugins-ext/` (e.g. `make plugins` dropping bundles into
# `plugins-ext/dist/`) from waking the watcher and rebuilding the GUI.

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Build artefacts (host + every nested workspace)
target/
**/target/

# Isolated target dir for the `bv-plugin-pack` packer/signer
# (see PLUGINS_PACK_TARGET_DIR in the Makefile).
target-plugin-pack/

# Reference-plugins submodule — a separate cargo workspace we depend on
# as built artefacts (uploaded at runtime), never as live source. Its
# source edits and `dist/` build outputs must not rebuild the GUI.
plugins-ext/

# IronRDP git submodule — path/git dep, not live source.
IronRDP/

# Generated docs / dist trees
docs/_build/
gui/dist/

# Tracking / documentation markdown — CHANGELOG.md, roadmap.md, agent.md,
# features/*.md, roadmaps/*.md — is edited constantly as part of the
# workflow (see agent.md's tracking rules) and never compiled into the
# binary, so writes here must not wake the watcher and rebuild the GUI.
# A stray rebuild mid-release also cancels the in-flight code-signing
# step (the FIDO2/CTAP PIN prompt), so keep all markdown out of the watch
# set. (Repo .md embedded via include_str! is only README.md under `doc`
# cfg in the IronRDP/third_party submodules, which are ignored anyway.)
**/*.md
